<p><b><a name="emergency_poison_information" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>The following information is from the <a href="http://www.1-800-222-1222.info/poisonHelp.asp" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');popupWarning();" target="_blank">American Association of Poison Control Centers (AAPCC)</a>.</p>.<p>The United States National Poison Hotline is <b>1-800-222-1222</b>. When you call this number you will be automatically linked to the nearest poison center in the United States. Call this number 24 hours a day, 7 days a week to talk to a poison expert.</p>.<p><b><a name="has_the_person_collapsed_or_stopped_breathing" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="has_the_person_swallowed_the_wrong_medicine_or_too_much_medicine" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="has_the_person_inhaled_poison" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="is_there_poison_on_the_persons_skin" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p><b><a name="is_there_poison_in_the_persons_eyes" class="bookmark"></a></b></p>.<p>We recommend that you print out a hard 
copy of this number and place it near your home/business phone(s) for easy 
access in a poison emergency.<span id="cntid"></span></p>